			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Job Description<br />
	<br />
	The Project Manager is responsible for the day-to-day delivery of client deliverables.&nbsp; The Project Manager guides projects through planning, strategic, creative and development phases.&nbsp; The Project Manager will work closely with the Account Management team, insuring that all deliverables remain on target, in budget, and on-time. He or she must be knowledgeable in both the client&rsquo;s business and the agency business. An effective problem-solver on a day-to-day basis, the Project Manager must be adept at anticipating problems and recognizing opportunities. As a member of a small but quickly growing agency, the project manager must be ready to immerse him or herself in a highly accountable, highly visible role. The Project Manager will report to a Project Director.<br />
	<br />
	<br />
	Duties and Responsibilities<br />
	<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Works closely with all agency department staff to develop and implement strategic project plans<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Has a thorough understanding of the planning, creative and production processes<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proactively gathers the necessary information to plan and implement each client project<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Provides timely issuance of all documentation: proposals, project initiations, creative briefs, estimates, timelines, meeting summaries, and status and budget reports<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages time and financial resources to ensure client projects are on time and on budget.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages project schedules<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Produces client budgets and estimate updates<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ensures project deliverables are delivered on time and on budget<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages internal and external resources<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Manages internal and external communication and documentation<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Works in a proactive manner to provide client campaigns with the greatest amount of added value through communications<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Gathers and assembles background information and analyses as needed in development of briefs, etc.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Receives client briefings from the Account Management team in order to execute in the most efficient and effective way possible<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Keeps apprised of all relevant client, industry and market developments<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Coordinates project timing and budgets with all relevant agency personnel.<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Continuously works to upgrade knowledge and skills through available reading, courses and seminars<br />
	&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Maintain a highly responsive service orientation in all transactions<br />
	<br />
	<br />
	Requirements:<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Minimum 2-5 years experience in a project management role. Agency experience a plus.<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Must be EXTREMELY organized, detailed and accurate<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to multi-task in a fast paced work environment, working well under pressure juggling multiple projects and deadlines<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Responsive to internal needs in a timely, professional manner<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Resolves and/or escalates issues in a timely fashion<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong business writing, communication, and interpersonal skills<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Proactive, self-starter who can work as part of a team primarily and independently when needed<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Experience or knowledge of creative and/or technical development process<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Highly skilled in building and managing project schedules and timelines<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to oversee programs through project lifecycle, ensuring deliverables are met on time<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Strong social media experience and a true passion for the space<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Solution oriented, problem-solving approach<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to grasp complex concepts easily<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Ability to operate in a systematic and logical manner, with use of good judgment<br />
	-&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Advanced experience with MS Project, Merlin, Basecamp, or other Project Management tools<br />
	<br />
