			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Position Overview  </p>
<p>
	The User Experience Strategist (UX Strategist) is responsible for the successful development of engaging interactive experiences for client brands, using digital, social media and mobile platforms. The role requires an experienced and versatile individual with the relationship skills to lead an internal team and to act as a key client-facing point of contact.</p>
<p>
	As a member of a growing agency with a distinctly unique approach to social media, the UX Strategist will play a highly accountable and visible role both internally and externally - from identifying and prioritizing client requirements to defining an optimal user experience that takes into account the specific behavior differences of social network users.</p>
<p>
	This person must have a passion for digital trends and innovation, combined with a sound understanding of consumers, social networks and brands. This person excels at identifying the middle point where client business objectives harmoniously meet consumer engagement and excitement.</p>
<p>
	Reports to: VP, Strategy  </p>
<p>
	Responsibilities overview  </p>
<p>
	The User Experience Strategist&#39;s primary responsibility is to help project teams develop and implement experiences driven by value exchanges between consumers / users and brands / businesses.</p>
<p>
	He/she is an expert at defining how brands are communicated and experienced through digital and social interactions, and at integrating digital and social interactions within broader customer experiences.</p>
<p>
	During the initial planning phase, this person evaluates consumer research, brand information, trends and relevant data in order to foster elegant and creative solutions that marry brand goals with consumer needs. During the implementation phase, the User Experience Strategist provides guidance to multi-disciplinary teams of account and project managers, software engineers, digital designers at key project milestones, ensuring that the outcome reflects closely the client-approved strategy.</p>
<p>
	You would be expected in particular to: <br />
	&bull; Develop, define and articulate business and user strategies for social platforms, global content consolidation, social and mobile applications.<br />
	&bull; Analyze user needs, behaviors, segmentations and develop personas<br />
	&bull; Define business, brand and marketing requirements, KPIs and metrics<br />
	&bull; Develop documentation, wireframes and presentations<br />
	&bull; Get buy-in from key clients around content and information proposals</p>
<p>
	&bull; Educate clients and colleagues around new digital technologies and trends</p>
<p>
	&bull; Work with client services team to identify key opportunities with both existing and prospective clients.  </p>
<p>
	&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Requirements:  </p>
<p>
	&bull; Strong knowledge of and interest in social media <br />
	&bull; Minimum of 8-10 years of user interaction design and information architecture, ideally in a marketing services / agency environment <br />
	&bull; Prior experience in developing requirements documents, wireframes, presentations <br />
	&bull; Prior experience in leading client-facing engagements <br />
	&bull; Adept at extracting meaningful insights from multiple sources of data<br />
	&bull; Ability to grasp complex concepts and systems quickly, and express them in simple ways <br />
	&bull; Strong business writing, storytelling, communication, presentation skills <br />
	&bull; Strong interpersonal and client relationship skills <br />
	&bull; Ability to operate in a systematic and logical manner, with use of good judgment <br />
